  "prompt": "What is the best answer I can give my girl when she asks me how are you?",
  "response": "The best answer you can give depends on how you're truly feeling and the nature of your relationship. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. If you're feeling good:\n   - \"I'm doing great, especially now that I'm talking to you.\"\n   - \"I'm really well, thanks for asking! How about you?\"\n\n2. If you're feeling okay but nothing special:\n   - \"I'm doing alright, thanks. How about you?\"\n   - \"I'm okay, just taking things one day at a time.\"\n\n3. If you're feeling down or stressed:\n   - \"I've been better, but talking to you always helps.\"\n   - \"I'm a bit stressed/tired, but I'm glad you asked.\"\n\nIt's always best to be honest and open with your feelings, as it fosters trust and deeper connection in your relationship.",
